n setup requirements**\\n\\nThe prompt is asking if additional setup is necessary beyond the normal generated scaffold for achieving meaningful coverage. I should choose no_action unless extra setup is really needed, which seems to be the case here. I might want to reference some artifact research in a concise summary, but it should be brief. I’ll note the risks, mentioning that while docs often use YAML requiring hoplite-yaml, the core library has built-in support, so extra modules aren't necessary. I need to make sure the final output is just valid JSON without any markdown formatting.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"hoplite-core is self-contained for meaningful core coverage: it brings Kotlin reflection/coroutines transitively, includes the built-in properties parser, and exposes Map/System/Environment property sources plus default decoders without requiring Docker or external services.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Documentation examples often use YAML/JSON/HOCON, which require optional Hoplite format modules, but those are not necessary to cover hoplite-core itself.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_095f3c095f05cbef016a4276a60b148193957ff394153d0dc8\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1275, "output": 640, "cacheRead": 47104, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 49019, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782740635141, "responseId": "resp_095f3c095f05cbef016a42769bb0a48193901c541cfeee2809"}, "toolResults": []}
